(3.1 Canal Desilting) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(  The accumulated silt, organic debris, and weed growth in the canal bed and) Tj T*
(  banks shall be removed using the following methods:) Tj T*
(  \(a\) Mechanical desilting using excavator + tipper \(for main canal bed\)) Tj T*
(  \(b\) Manual desilting and basket removal \(for reaches inaccessible to machinery\)) Tj T*
(  Excavated silt to be disposed at designated spoil sites approved by CNNL.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(3.2 Embankment Restoration) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(  Embankment cross-sections shall be restored to design dimensions \(FSL, bank) Tj T*
(  width 2.4 m, side slope 1:1.5\). Settlement or erosion pockets to be made) Tj T*
(  good with compacted earth \(proctor density   95%\).) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(3.3 Concrete Lining Repair) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(  Existing M15 CC lining to be repaired at 23 damaged locations \(total area) Tj T*
(  approx. 1,850 sqm\). Repair shall include:) Tj T*
(  \(a\) Removing loose/cracked panels) Tj T*
(  \(b\) Sub-grade compaction) Tj T*
(  \(c\) Providing 75 mm M15 CC lining with 3 mm plaster finish) Tj T*
(  \(d\) Expansion joints with bitumen felt at 6 m centres) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(3.4 Cross-Drainage Structures) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(  Reconstruction of 4 cross-drainage sluices \(rectangular box type, 0.6 m) Tj T*
(  opening, head wall and tail wall in M20 CC, wooden shutters\). Co-ordination) Tj T*
(  with CNNL's hydraulic engineer for gate setting.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(3.5 Field Channel Desilting) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(  Manual desilting of 6 field channels \(total 6.2 km\). Silt disposal at) Tj T*
(  farmer's field or spoil site as directed by field engineer.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(================================================================================) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(4. ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA) Tj T*
(================================================================================) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(IMPORTANT: Bids from contractors not meeting ALL the eligibility criteria listed) Tj T*
(below will be summarily rejected at the technical evaluation stage. Waivers) Tj T*
(will not be granted.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(4.1 Annual Turnover) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(  The bidder shall have an Average Annual Turnover not less than Rs. 2.00 Crore) Tj T*
(  from civil or irrigation works during the last 3 \(three\) financial years) Tj T*
(  \(2023-24, 2024-25, 2025-26\).) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(  Supporting documents: Audited Profit & Loss Statement and Balance Sheet for) Tj T*
(  last 3 financial years, certified by a Chartered Accountant.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(4.2 Technical Experience   Similar Canal / Irrigation Works) Tj T*
() Tj T*
ET
endstream
